<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1987,2014]" box="[151,1436,1987,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">
This family is represented in the Neotropics by five genera and about 315 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R." box="[1035,1315,1987,2013]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" pagination="1 - 566" refId="ref5887" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R. (2017) Catalog of the Neotropical Trichoptera (Caddisflies). Zookeys, 654, 1 - 566. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 654.9516" type="journal article" year="2017">Holzenthal &amp;Calor 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Camargos, L. M." box="[1323,1436,1987,2013]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" refId="ref5180" refString="Camargos, L. M. (2020) Systematics of Cernotina Ross and Cyrnellus Banks (Insecta: Trichoptera: Polycentropodidae). Ph. D. thesis, University of Minnesota, St. Paul, Minnesota, USA, 321 pp." type="book" year="2020">Camargos</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="584" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">
2020). In 
<collectingCountry box="[261,353,151,177]" name="Panama" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 24 species are known, distributed among four genera: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ross" authorityYear="1938" box="[971,1085,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Cernotina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[971,1085,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">Cernotina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
